00:41:35.640 --> 00:41:36.540
You talked a little bit about

00:41:36.540 --> 00:41:39.260
expenditures and some of those--

00:41:39.260 --> 00:41:40.000
JOHN WOOD: OK.

00:41:40.000 --> 00:41:41.120
Can you rephrase?

00:41:41.120 --> 00:41:41.195
SUSAN WOJCICKI: Yeah.

00:41:41.195 --> 00:41:45.810
So the question was basically
you'd have a lot of success

00:41:45.810 --> 00:41:48.340
because of being very data
driven and from the experience

00:41:48.340 --> 00:41:51.300
